Usage: write_macro_place_constraint [-help]
                                    [-cpg_scope {selected macro_only all}]
                                    -out_file <string>
                                    [-sections {array basic cpg pg_model_over_macros pg_resource_model net_length net_resistance}]

-help                                    # Prints out the command usage
-cpg_scope {selected macro_only all}     # specify which instances to be
                                         # written in cpg guide section
                                         # (enum, optional)
-out_file <string>                       # write macro place constraints to the
                                         # specified file (string, required)
-sections {array basic cpg pg_model_over_macros pg_resource_model net_length net_resistance}
                                         # specify the constraint sections to
                                         # dump (enum_list, optional)